This paper is about natural language generation (NLG) using deep neural networks (DNNs), which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of self-training and noise injection sampling to improve the performance of NLG models, which are topics that are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the evaluation of the models using automatic and human evaluations, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SD) as it pertains to the development and testing of software systems.
